15:37.067 --> 15:39.861
Whoa! Whoa, sir! Sir?
Turn around.

15:39.945 --> 15:43.990
Sir, you have no right to claim
ownership of another person's work.

15:44.074 --> 15:46.493
- Who are you?
- I'm a lawyer.

15:46.576 --> 15:48.411
You have a lawyer?

15:48.495 --> 15:50.789
It is one thing to lie,

15:50.872 --> 15:53.458
but then to bully this young man—
It's unforgivable.

15:53.583 --> 15:55.561
[ Chattering Stops ] And this is
what's wrong with the world today.

15:55.585 --> 15:57.671
The big guy...

15:57.754 --> 15:59.732
thinks that he can roll
right over the little guy...

15:59.756 --> 16:03.009
until the little guy says,
“Enough?

16:03.093 --> 16:05.095
And that's what
this little guy's doing...

16:05.178 --> 16:07.347
Right here, right now.

16:07.430 --> 16:09.867
Can we stop calling me “little
guy”? I'm in the 40th percentile.

16:09.891 --> 16:11.935
Shh. I got this.

16:12.018 --> 16:15.605
Ted Durkas clearly
did not write that poem.

16:15.689 --> 16:18.817
<i>I know it.
He knows it.</i>

16:18.900 --> 16:20.986
<i>Deep down in your heart, Fiona—</i>

16:21.069 --> 16:23.405
[ Exhales]
you know it too.

16:28.493 --> 16:30.912
Shame!

16:30.996 --> 16:32.998
Fine! Whatever.
I stole his stupid poem.

16:33.081 --> 16:34.958
- <i>[Fiona ] You did?</i>
- I told you.

16:35.041 --> 16:36.501
There you go.

16:36.585 --> 16:39.421
<i>I only did it
because I had the feelings,</i>

16:39.504 --> 16:41.298
I just didn't know
how to show <i>'em.</i>

16:41.381 --> 16:46.428
Really? That's the sweetest
thing anyone's ever done for me.

16:46.511 --> 16:48.263
You've gotta be kidding me.

16:48.346 --> 16:51.349
- Let's get out of here. This Chick's crazy.
- Seriously.

16:51.433 --> 16:53.351
I've never seen you like that.

16:53.435 --> 16:55.103
You have no idea
how good that felt.

16:55.187 --> 16:58.106
Well, happy Valentine's Day,
counselor.

16:58.315 --> 17:00.859
This is all happening
so fast, Juliana.

17:00.942 --> 17:03.904
I know, and I have to be home
to my husband by midnight.

17:03.987 --> 17:06.239
Ooh, a twist.

17:08.491 --> 17:11.036
Phil!
Phil, my coat is stuck.

17:11.161 --> 17:12.787
Who's Phil? No,
not now! Seriously.

17:12.913 --> 17:15.081
My coat is stuck. Oh, oh.
Honey, take off your coat!

17:15.207 --> 17:17.500
Are you kidding me?
Pull it. Oh, my goodness.

17:17.584 --> 17:19.878
Pull it.
Come on. Come on.

17:19.961 --> 17:22.047
[ Claire ] Oh, boy.
Not good. Not good.

17:22.130 --> 17:23.882
<i>[ Buzzer Sounds ]
[ Escalator Stops ]</i>

17:23.965 --> 17:26.551
[ Gasps ]
Okay. Okay. Okay.

17:26.635 --> 17:28.595
Come on up. Treat 'em like
they're regular stairs.

17:28.678 --> 17:30.347
It's okay.
Come on through.

17:30.430 --> 17:32.891
Happy Valentine's Day.
You look lovely.

17:32.974 --> 17:35.018
So do you. Not in
a weird way. Yeah.

17:35.143 --> 17:36.728
How are you? Hi.
Hi.

17:36.811 --> 17:39.207
Happy Valentine's— Let me just
get in here. Let me get in here.

17:39.231 --> 17:40.273
Okay?
Phil?

17:40.398 --> 17:41.983
Hey, Tom.
Hi.

17:42.067 --> 17:43.860
How are you? Honey...

17:43.944 --> 17:46.744
Claire, you remember Tom Mickleson
from the office and his wife, Susan.

17:46.863 --> 17:49.449
I do. Hey.
Is your coat stuck?

17:49.532 --> 17:53.078
It is. It really is.
It's in there pretty darn good.

17:53.203 --> 17:57.457
Why don't you take it
off? Um, I'm freezing cold.

17:57.540 --> 17:59.000
At least let me give it a shot.

17:59.125 --> 18:01.711
[Phil] Oh, I don't think—
No, no, no. I got it.

18:01.836 --> 18:03.380
<i>Mr. and Mrs. Dunphy?
Hey.</i>

18:03.505 --> 18:06.049
Principal Balaban.
Hey, how are you?

18:06.174 --> 18:08.677
<i>[ Claire ]</i> Hi.
Who's Clive Bixby?

18:08.760 --> 18:11.972
Oh, uh, he makes speakers.

18:12.097 --> 18:14.432
He's actually in town
for a trade show. Phil.

18:14.557 --> 18:17.727
<i>My, are you stuck?
Yeah, I am. A little bit.</i>

18:17.852 --> 18:20.105
Why don't you take off
that coat? Um, I'm chilly.

18:20.188 --> 18:22.065
It's really jammed in here.

18:22.190 --> 18:24.776
Let me in there. I'll get
you. No, I think we're okay.

18:24.859 --> 18:26.903
<i>Mrs. Dunphy?</i>

18:26.987 --> 18:29.114
Are you kidding me?

18:29.197 --> 18:32.200
Hi! Luke's math teacher,
Ms. Passwater.

18:32.284 --> 18:33.952
[ Chuckling ]
“Passwater.”

18:34.035 --> 18:35.537
<i>[ Laughter, Applause ]</i>

18:35.620 --> 18:38.415
Ah, Jay, <i>Pap/I</i> don't pay
attention to what he's saying.

18:38.540 --> 18:40.959
He's just being funny.
Because he points out the truth.

18:41.042 --> 18:44.045
Those people were laughing
because they saw it too.

18:44.170 --> 18:46.506
What do you care
what they think? I don't.

18:46.589 --> 18:48.633
I care what you think.

18:48.758 --> 18:51.261
I love you. You're my
valentine. Yeah, for now.

18:51.344 --> 18:54.347
But what about when I'm 80 and
I'm in a wheelchair, on oxygen?

18:54.431 --> 18:55.932
You still gonna want me?

18:56.016 --> 18:59.352
Do you think I'm so shallow that
I'm gonna leave you when you're old?

18:59.436 --> 19:02.188
What if I gain a hundred
pounds? You gonna leave me then?

19:03.231 --> 19:06.192
No.
What's with the pause?

19:06.276 --> 19:09.029
Well, it's not exactly fair.
I mean, I have to get old.

19:09.154 --> 19:11.990
You don't have to get fat.
If I want to get fat, I get fat.

19:12.073 --> 19:14.153
Okay, fine. And if you do,
I'll be there. You'll see.

19:14.200 --> 19:16.828
Yeah, watch me.
Watch me, how I get fat.

19:16.953 --> 19:20.248
I can get fat.
And I'll be there.

19:21.291 --> 19:23.752
[Laughs]
Good.

19:23.877 --> 19:25.795
You wanna go back in?
No.

19:25.879 --> 19:27.839
I got a better idea.

19:27.922 --> 19:30.508
Let's go salsa dancing.
This guy's not that funny.

19:30.592 --> 19:32.802
[ Gasps ]
Perfect.

19:34.637 --> 19:36.848
<i>We're good! We're good!
I talked to Maintenance.</i>

19:36.931 --> 19:39.059
They're— They're—
They're coming, so go on ahead.

19:39.142 --> 19:41.561
<i>See you guys.
See you later.</i>

19:41.644 --> 19:43.688
See you in school.
Good to see you guys.

19:43.772 --> 19:45.398
Maintenance is gonna
take care of it.

19:45.523 --> 19:48.610
So we're fine. Okay. Okay,
how long till they get here?

19:48.693 --> 19:50.695
I was faking it.
No one's coming for us.

19:50.779 --> 19:52.781
Well, then, go and get them!
Hurry!

19:52.864 --> 19:55.575
That was the most
embarrassing moment of my life.

19:55.658 --> 19:57.619
Claire! Phil!

19:57.702 --> 20:00.455
Stand by.

20:00.538 --> 20:02.290
Hey.

20:02.374 --> 20:04.959
- What, did you get your belt stuck?
- I did. Yeah.

20:05.043 --> 20:06.645
Take your coat off.
Here, let me help you.

20:06.669 --> 20:08.505
No, no, Dad. Dad,
I'm fine. <i>Come</i> on!

20:08.588 --> 20:10.256
What are you, naked under there?

20:11.716 --> 20:14.594
Aw, geez.
It's okay.

20:14.677 --> 20:17.055
I got this.
<i>Okay.</i>

20:17.138 --> 20:19.099
Claire, follow my lead, okay?

20:20.308 --> 20:21.976
Okay.

20:28.400 --> 20:30.151
<i>[ Claire ]
Wow. Okay.</i>

20:31.236 --> 20:34.531
Thank you. It has
happened to me before.

20:34.614 --> 20:37.033
That was impressive.

20:37.117 --> 20:39.452
Take it down a notch, Clive.

20:40.495 --> 20:42.705
<i>[ Phil ] You okay?
Yeah. I'm good.</i>

20:42.831 --> 20:44.082
All right.
I'm good.

20:44.165 --> 20:45.976
Happy Valentine's Day.
[Claire] Happy Valentine's Day.

20:46.000 --> 20:47.335
<i>Chao.</i>
Okay. See ya.

20:47.460 --> 20:48.628
Bye.
Good night.

20:48.753 --> 20:50.463
Oh. That's—
[Laughs]

20:50.547 --> 20:53.508
Sorry.
See you, guys.

